447 // gets emitted by the asmprinter. ----
448 MachineModuleInfoImpl::StubValueTy &StubSym = ELFMMI.getGVStubEntry(SSym); 0
449 if (!StubSym.getPointer()) { 0
450 MCSymbol *Sym = TM.getSymbol(GV); 0
451 StubSym = MachineModuleInfoImpl::StubValueTy(Sym, !GV->hasLocalLinkage()); 0
452 } ----

454 return TargetLoweringObjectFile:: ----
455 getTTypeReference(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(SSym, getContext()), 0
456 Encoding & ~DW_EH_PE_indirect, Streamer); 0
457 } ----
458 ----
459 return TargetLoweringObjectFile::getTTypeGlobalReference(GV, Encoding, TM, 0
460 MMI, Streamer); 0
461 } ----

463 static SectionKind getELFKindForNamedSection(StringRef Name, SectionKind K) { 0
464 // N.B.: The defaults used in here are not the same ones used in MC. ----
465 // We follow gcc, MC follows gas. For example, given ".section .eh_frame", ----
466 // both gas and MC will produce a section with no flags. Given ----
467 // section(".eh_frame") gcc will produce: ----
468 // ----
469 // .section .eh_frame,"a",@progbits ----
470 ----
471 if (Name == getInstrProfSectionName(IPSK_covmap, Triple::ELF, 0
472 /*AddSegmentInfo=*/false) || 0
473 Name == getInstrProfSectionName(IPSK_covfun, Triple::ELF, 0
474 /*AddSegmentInfo=*/false) || 0
475 Name == ".llvmbc" || Name == ".llvmcmd") 0
476 return SectionKind::getMetadata(); 0
477 ----
478 if (Name.empty() || Name[0] != '.') return K; 0
479 ----
480 // Default implementation based on some magic section names. ----
481 if (Name == ".bss" || 0
482 Name.startswith(".bss.") || 0
483 Name.startswith(".gnu.linkonce.b.") || 0
484 Name.startswith(".llvm.linkonce.b.") || 0
485 Name == ".sbss" || 0
486 Name.startswith(".sbss.") || 0
487 Name.startswith(".gnu.linkonce.sb.") || 0
488 Name.startswith(".llvm.linkonce.sb.")) 0
489 return SectionKind::getBSS(); 0
490 ----
491 if (Name == ".tdata" || 0
492 Name.startswith(".tdata.") || 0
493 Name.startswith(".gnu.linkonce.td.") || 0
494 Name.startswith(".llvm.linkonce.td.")) 0
495 return SectionKind::getThreadData(); 0
496 ----
497 if (Name == ".tbss" || 0
498 Name.startswith(".tbss.") || 0
499 Name.startswith(".gnu.linkonce.tb.") || 0
500 Name.startswith(".llvm.linkonce.tb.")) 0
501 return SectionKind::getThreadBSS(); 0
502 ----
503 return K; 0
504 } ----

591 static unsigned getEntrySizeForKind(SectionKind Kind) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
592 if (Kind.isMergeable1ByteCString()) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
593 return 1; 0
594 else if (Kind.isMergeable2ByteCString()) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
595 return 2; 0

597 return 4; 0
598 else if (Kind.isMergeableConst4()) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

602 else if (Kind.isMergeableConst16()) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
603 return 16; 0
604 else if (Kind.isMergeableConst32()) 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
605 return 32; 0
606 else { ----
607 // We shouldn't have mergeable C strings or mergeable constants that we ----
608 // didn't handle above. ----
609 assert(!Kind.isMergeableCString() && "unknown string width"); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
610 assert(!Kind.isMergeableConst() && "unknown data width"); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
611 return 0; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
612 } ----

678 class LoweringDiagnosticInfo : public DiagnosticInfo { ----
679 const Twine &Msg; ----
680 ----
681 public: ----
682 LoweringDiagnosticInfo(const Twine &DiagMsg, 0

689 /// Calculate an appropriate unique ID for a section, and update Flags, ----
690 /// EntrySize and NextUniqueID where appropriate. ----
691 static unsigned ----
692 calcUniqueIDUpdateFlagsAndSize(const GlobalObject *GO, StringRef SectionName, 0
693 SectionKind Kind, const TargetMachine &TM, ----
694 MCContext &Ctx, Mangler &Mang, unsigned &Flags, ----
695 unsigned &EntrySize, unsigned &NextUniqueID, ----
696 const bool Retain, const bool ForceUnique) { ----
697 // Increment uniqueID if we are forced to emit a unique section. ----
698 // This works perfectly fine with section attribute or pragma section as the ----
699 // sections with the same name are grouped together by the assembler. ----
700 if (ForceUnique) 0
701 return NextUniqueID++; 0
702 ----
703 // A section can have at most one associated section. Put each global with ----
704 // MD_associated in a unique section. ----
705 const bool Associated = GO->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_associated); 0
706 if (Associated) { 0
707 Flags |= ELF::SHF_LINK_ORDER; 0
708 return NextUniqueID++; 0
709 } ----
710 ----
711 if (Retain) { 0
712 if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSSolaris()) 0
713 Flags |= ELF::SHF_SUNW_NODISCARD; 0
714 else if (Ctx.getAsmInfo()->useIntegratedAssembler() || 0
715 Ctx.getAsmInfo()->binutilsIsAtLeast(2, 36)) 0
716 Flags |= ELF::SHF_GNU_RETAIN; 0
717 return NextUniqueID++; 0
718 } ----
719 ----
720 // If two symbols with differing sizes end up in the same mergeable section ----
721 // that section can be assigned an incorrect entry size. To avoid this we ----
722 // usually put symbols of the same size into distinct mergeable sections with ----
723 // the same name. Doing so relies on the ",unique ," assembly feature. This ----
724 // feature is not avalible until bintuils version 2.35 ----
725 // (https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=25380). ----
726 const bool SupportsUnique = Ctx.getAsmInfo()->useIntegratedAssembler() || 0
727 Ctx.getAsmInfo()->binutilsIsAtLeast(2, 35); 0
728 if (!SupportsUnique) { 0
729 Flags &= ~ELF::SHF_MERGE; 0
730 EntrySize = 0; 0
731 return MCContext::GenericSectionID; 0
732 } ----
733 ----
734 const bool SymbolMergeable = Flags & ELF::SHF_MERGE; 0
735 const bool SeenSectionNameBefore = ----
736 Ctx.isELFGenericMergeableSection(SectionName); 0
737 // If this is the first ocurrence of this section name, treat it as the ----
738 // generic section ----
739 if (!SymbolMergeable && !SeenSectionNameBefore) 0
740 return MCContext::GenericSectionID; 0
741 ----
742 // Symbols must be placed into sections with compatible entry sizes. Generate ----
743 // unique sections for symbols that have not been assigned to compatible ----
744 // sections. ----
745 const auto PreviousID = ----
746 Ctx.getELFUniqueIDForEntsize(SectionName, Flags, EntrySize); 0
747 if (PreviousID) 0
748 return *PreviousID; 0
749 ----
750 // If the user has specified the same section name as would be created ----
751 // implicitly for this symbol e.g. .rodata.str1.1, then we don't need ----
752 // to unique the section as the entry size for this symbol will be ----
753 // compatible with implicitly created sections. ----
754 SmallString<128> ImplicitSectionNameStem = ----
755 getELFSectionNameForGlobal(GO, Kind, Mang, TM, EntrySize, false); 0
756 if (SymbolMergeable && 0
757 Ctx.isELFImplicitMergeableSectionNamePrefix(SectionName) && 0
758 SectionName.startswith(ImplicitSectionNameStem)) 0
759 return MCContext::GenericSectionID; 0
760 ----
761 // We have seen this section name before, but with different flags or entity ----
762 // size. Create a new unique ID. ----
763 return NextUniqueID++; 0
764 } 0
765 ----
766 static MCSection *selectExplicitSectionGlobal( 0
767 const GlobalObject *GO, SectionKind Kind, const TargetMachine &TM, ----
768 MCContext &Ctx, Mangler &Mang, unsigned &NextUniqueID, ----
769 bool Retain, bool ForceUnique) { ----
770 StringRef SectionName = GO->getSection(); 0
771 ----
772 // Check if '#pragma clang section' name is applicable. ----
773 // Note that pragma directive overrides -ffunction-section, -fdata-section ----
774 // and so section name is exactly as user specified and not uniqued. ----
775 const GlobalVariable *GV = dyn_cast(GO); 0
776 if (GV && GV->hasImplicitSection()) { 0
777 auto Attrs = GV->getAttributes(); 0
778 if (Attrs.hasAttribute("bss-section") && Kind.isBSS()) { 0
779 SectionName = Attrs.getAttribute("bss-section").getValueAsString(); 0
780 } else if (Attrs.hasAttribute("rodata-section") && Kind.isReadOnly()) { 0
781 SectionName = Attrs.getAttribute("rodata-section").getValueAsString(); 0
782 } else if (Attrs.hasAttribute("relro-section") && Kind.isReadOnlyWithRel()) { 0
783 SectionName = Attrs.getAttribute("relro-section").getValueAsString(); 0
784 } else if (Attrs.hasAttribute("data-section") && Kind.isData()) { 0
785 SectionName = Attrs.getAttribute("data-section").getValueAsString(); 0
786 } ----
787 } ----
788 const Function *F = dyn_cast(GO); 0
789 if (F && F->hasFnAttribute("implicit-section-name")) { 0
790 SectionName = F->getFnAttribute("implicit-section-name").getValueAsString(); 0
791 } ----
792 ----
793 // Infer section flags from the section name if we can. ----
794 Kind = getELFKindForNamedSection(SectionName, Kind); 0
795 ----
796 StringRef Group = ""; 0
797 bool IsComdat = false; 0
798 unsigned Flags = getELFSectionFlags(Kind); 0
799 if (const Comdat *C = getELFComdat(GO)) { 0
800 Group = C->getName(); 0
801 IsComdat = C->getSelectionKind() == Comdat::Any; 0
802 Flags |= ELF::SHF_GROUP; 0
803 } ----
804 ----
805 unsigned EntrySize = getEntrySizeForKind(Kind); 0
806 const unsigned UniqueID = calcUniqueIDUpdateFlagsAndSize( 0
807 GO, SectionName, Kind, TM, Ctx, Mang, Flags, EntrySize, NextUniqueID, ----
808 Retain, ForceUnique); ----
809 ----
810 const MCSymbolELF *LinkedToSym = getLinkedToSymbol(GO, TM); 0
811 MCSectionELF *Section = Ctx.getELFSection( 0
812 SectionName, getELFSectionType(SectionName, Kind), Flags, EntrySize, ----
813 Group, IsComdat, UniqueID, LinkedToSym); ----
814 // Make sure that we did not get some other section with incompatible sh_link. ----
815 // This should not be possible due to UniqueID code above. ----
816 assert(Section->getLinkedToSymbol() == LinkedToSym && 0
817 "Associated symbol mismatch between sections"); ----
818 ----
819 if (!(Ctx.getAsmInfo()->useIntegratedAssembler() || 0
820 Ctx.getAsmInfo()->binutilsIsAtLeast(2, 35))) { 0
821 // If we are using GNU as before 2.35, then this symbol might have ----
822 // been placed in an incompatible mergeable section. Emit an error if this ----
823 // is the case to avoid creating broken output. ----
824 if ((Section->getFlags() & ELF::SHF_MERGE) && 0
825 (Section->getEntrySize() != getEntrySizeForKind(Kind))) 0
826 GO->getContext().diagnose(LoweringDiagnosticInfo( 0
827 "Symbol '" + GO->getName() + "' from module '" + 0
828 (GO->getParent() ? GO->getParent()->getSourceFileName() : "unknown") + 0
829 "' required a section with entry-size=" + 0
830 Twine(getEntrySizeForKind(Kind)) + " but was placed in section '" + 0
831 SectionName + "' with entry-size=" + Twine(Section->getEntrySize()) + 0
832 ": Explicit assignment by pragma or attribute of an incompatible " ----
833 "symbol to this section?")); 0
834 } ----
835 ----
836 return Section; 0
837 } ----
838 ----
839 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileELF::getExplicitSectionGlobal( 0
840 const GlobalObject *GO, SectionKind Kind, const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
841 return selectExplicitSectionGlobal(GO, Kind, TM, getContext(), getMangler(), 0
842 NextUniqueID, Used.count(GO), 0
843 /* ForceUnique = */false); 0
844 } ----

965 ----
966 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileELF::getSectionForLSDA( 0
967 const Function &F, const MCSymbol &FnSym, const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
968 // If neither COMDAT nor function sections, use the monolithic LSDA section. ----
969 // Re-use this path if LSDASection is null as in the Arm EHABI. ----
970 if (!LSDASection || (!F.hasComdat() && !TM.getFunctionSections())) 0
971 return LSDASection; 0
972 ----
973 const auto *LSDA = cast(LSDASection); 0
974 unsigned Flags = LSDA->getFlags(); 0
975 const MCSymbolELF *LinkedToSym = nullptr; 0
976 StringRef Group; 0
977 bool IsComdat = false; 0
978 if (const Comdat *C = getELFComdat(&F)) { 0
979 Flags |= ELF::SHF_GROUP; 0
980 Group = C->getName(); 0
981 IsComdat = C->getSelectionKind() == Comdat::Any; 0
982 } ----
983 // Use SHF_LINK_ORDER to facilitate --gc-sections if we can use GNU ld>=2.36 ----
984 // or LLD, which support mixed SHF_LINK_ORDER & non-SHF_LINK_ORDER. ----
985 if (TM.getFunctionSections() && 0
986 (getContext().getAsmInfo()->useIntegratedAssembler() && 0
987 getContext().getAsmInfo()->binutilsIsAtLeast(2, 36))) { 0
988 Flags |= ELF::SHF_LINK_ORDER; 0
989 LinkedToSym = cast(&FnSym); 0
990 } ----
991 ----
992 // Append the function name as the suffix like GCC, assuming ----
993 // -funique-section-names applies to .gcc_except_table sections. ----
994 return getContext().getELFSection( 0
995 (TM.getUniqueSectionNames() ? LSDA->getName() + "." + F.getName() 0
996 : LSDA->getName()), 0
997 LSDA->getType(), Flags, 0, Group, IsComdat, MCSection::NonUniqueID, ----
998 LinkedToSym); 0
999 } ----

1003 // We can always create relative relocations, so use another section ----
1004 // that can be marked non-executable. ----
1005 return false; 0
1006 } ----

1010 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileELF::getSectionForConstant( 0

1012 Align &Alignment) const { ----
1013 if (Kind.isMergeableConst4() && MergeableConst4Section) 0

1015 if (Kind.isMergeableConst8() && MergeableConst8Section) 0

1028 /// Returns a unique section for the given machine basic block. ----
1029 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileELF::getSectionForMachineBasicBlock( 0
1030 const Function &F, const MachineBasicBlock &MBB, ----
1031 const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
1032 assert(MBB.isBeginSection() && "Basic block does not start a section!"); 0
1033 unsigned UniqueID = MCContext::GenericSectionID; 0
1034 ----
1035 // For cold sections use the .text.split. prefix along with the parent ----
1036 // function name. All cold blocks for the same function go to the same ----
1037 // section. Similarly all exception blocks are grouped by symbol name ----
1038 // under the .text.eh prefix. For regular sections, we either use a unique ----
1039 // name, or a unique ID for the section. ----
1040 SmallString<128> Name; 0
1041 if (MBB.getSectionID() == MBBSectionID::ColdSectionID) { 0
1042 Name += BBSectionsColdTextPrefix; 0
1043 Name += MBB.getParent()->getName(); 0
1044 } else if (MBB.getSectionID() == MBBSectionID::ExceptionSectionID) { 0
1045 Name += ".text.eh."; 0
1046 Name += MBB.getParent()->getName(); 0
1047 } else { ----
1048 Name += MBB.getParent()->getSection()->getName(); 0
1049 if (TM.getUniqueBasicBlockSectionNames()) { 0
1050 if (!Name.endswith(".")) 0
1051 Name += "."; 0
1052 Name += MBB.getSymbol()->getName(); 0
1053 } else { ----
1054 UniqueID = NextUniqueID++; 0
1055 } ----
1056 } ----
1057 ----
1058 unsigned Flags = ELF::SHF_ALLOC | ELF::SHF_EXECINSTR; 0
1059 std::string GroupName; 0
1060 if (F.hasComdat()) { 0
1061 Flags |= ELF::SHF_GROUP; 0
1062 GroupName = F.getComdat()->getName().str(); 0
1063 } ----
1064 return getContext().getELFSection(Name, ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, Flags, 0
1065 0 /* Entry Size */, GroupName, ----
1066 F.hasComdat(), UniqueID, nullptr); 0
1067 } 0
1068 ----
1069 static MCSectionELF *getStaticStructorSection(MCContext &Ctx, bool UseInitArray, 0
1070 bool IsCtor, unsigned Priority, ----
1071 const MCSymbol *KeySym) { ----
1072 std::string Name; 0
1073 unsigned Type; ----
1074 unsigned Flags = ELF::SHF_ALLOC | ELF::SHF_WRITE; 0
1075 StringRef Comdat = KeySym ? KeySym->getName() : ""; 0
1076 ----
1077 if (KeySym) 0
1078 Flags |= ELF::SHF_GROUP; 0
1079 ----
1080 if (UseInitArray) { 0
1081 if (IsCtor) { 0
1082 Type = ELF::SHT_INIT_ARRAY; 0
1083 Name = ".init_array"; 0
1084 } else { ----
1085 Type = ELF::SHT_FINI_ARRAY; 0
1086 Name = ".fini_array"; 0
1087 } ----
1088 if (Priority != 65535) { 0
1089 Name += '.'; 0
1090 Name += utostr(Priority); 0
1091 } ----
1092 } else { ----
1093 // The default scheme is .ctor / .dtor, so we have to invert the priority ----
1094 // numbering. ----
1095 if (IsCtor) 0
1096 Name = ".ctors"; 0
1097 else ----
1098 Name = ".dtors"; 0
1099 if (Priority != 65535) 0
1100 raw_string_ostream(Name) << format(".%05u", 65535 - Priority); 0
1101 Type = ELF::SHT_PROGBITS; 0
1102 } ----
1103 ----
1104 return Ctx.getELFSection(Name, Type, Flags, 0, Comdat, /*IsComdat=*/true); 0
1105 } 0

1111 } ----

1129 RHS->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() != 0 || LHS->isThreadLocal() || 0

1221 ----
1222 void TargetLoweringObjectFileMachO::emitModuleMetadata(MCStreamer &Streamer, 0
1223 Module &M) const { ----
1224 // Emit the linker options if present. ----
1225 if (auto *LinkerOptions = M.getNamedMetadata("llvm.linker.options")) { 0
1226 for (const auto *Option : LinkerOptions->operands()) { 0
1227 SmallVector StrOptions; 0
1228 for (const auto &Piece : cast(Option)->operands()) 0
1229 StrOptions.push_back(std::string(cast(Piece)->getString())); 0
1230 Streamer.emitLinkerOptions(StrOptions); 0
1231 } 0
1232 } ----
1233 ----
1234 unsigned VersionVal = 0; 0
1235 unsigned ImageInfoFlags = 0; 0
1236 StringRef SectionVal; 0
1237 ----
1238 GetObjCImageInfo(M, VersionVal, ImageInfoFlags, SectionVal); 0
1239 emitCGProfileMetadata(Streamer, M); 0
1240 ----
1241 // The section is mandatory. If we don't have it, then we don't have GC info. ----
1242 if (SectionVal.empty()) 0
1243 return; 0
1244 ----
1245 StringRef Segment, Section; 0
1246 unsigned TAA = 0, StubSize = 0; 0
1247 bool TAAParsed; ----
1248 if (Error E = MCSectionMachO::ParseSectionSpecifier( 0
1249 SectionVal, Segment, Section, TAA, TAAParsed, StubSize)) { 0
1250 // If invalid, report the error with report_fatal_error. ----
1251 report_fatal_error("Invalid section specifier '" + Section + 0
1252 "': " + toString(std::move(E)) + "."); 0
1253 } 0
1254 ----
1255 // Get the section. ----
1256 MCSectionMachO *S = getContext().getMachOSection( 0
1257 Segment, Section, TAA, StubSize, SectionKind::getData()); ----
1258 Streamer.switchSection(S); 0
1259 Streamer.emitLabel(getContext(). 0
1260 getOrCreateSymbol(StringRef("L_OBJC_IMAGE_INFO"))); 0
1261 Streamer.emitInt32(VersionVal); 0
1262 Streamer.emitInt32(ImageInfoFlags); 0
1263 Streamer.addBlankLine(); 0
1264 } ----
1265 ----
1266 static void checkMachOComdat(const GlobalValue *GV) { 0
1267 const Comdat *C = GV->getComdat(); 0
1268 if (!C) 0
1269 return; 0
1270 ----
1271 report_fatal_error("MachO doesn't support COMDATs, '" + C->getName() + 0
1272 "' cannot be lowered."); 0
1273 } ----
1274 ----
1275 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileMachO::getExplicitSectionGlobal( 0
1276 const GlobalObject *GO, SectionKind Kind, const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
1277 ----
1278 StringRef SectionName = GO->getSection(); 0
1279 ----
1280 const GlobalVariable *GV = dyn_cast(GO); 0
1281 if (GV && GV->hasImplicitSection()) { 0
1282 auto Attrs = GV->getAttributes(); 0
1283 if (Attrs.hasAttribute("bss-section") && Kind.isBSS()) { 0
1284 SectionName = Attrs.getAttribute("bss-section").getValueAsString(); 0
1285 } else if (Attrs.hasAttribute("rodata-section") && Kind.isReadOnly()) { 0
1286 SectionName = Attrs.getAttribute("rodata-section").getValueAsString(); 0
1287 } else if (Attrs.hasAttribute("relro-section") && Kind.isReadOnlyWithRel()) { 0
1288 SectionName = Attrs.getAttribute("relro-section").getValueAsString(); 0
1289 } else if (Attrs.hasAttribute("data-section") && Kind.isData()) { 0
1290 SectionName = Attrs.getAttribute("data-section").getValueAsString(); 0
1291 } ----
1292 } ----
1293 ----
1294 const Function *F = dyn_cast(GO); 0
1295 if (F && F->hasFnAttribute("implicit-section-name")) { 0
1296 SectionName = F->getFnAttribute("implicit-section-name").getValueAsString(); 0
1297 } ----
1298 ----
1299 // Parse the section specifier and create it if valid. ----
1300 StringRef Segment, Section; 0
1301 unsigned TAA = 0, StubSize = 0; 0
1302 bool TAAParsed; ----
1303 ----
1304 checkMachOComdat(GO); 0
1305 ----
1306 if (Error E = MCSectionMachO::ParseSectionSpecifier( 0
1307 SectionName, Segment, Section, TAA, TAAParsed, StubSize)) { 0
1308 // If invalid, report the error with report_fatal_error. ----
1309 report_fatal_error("Global variable '" + GO->getName() + 0
1310 "' has an invalid section specifier '" + 0
1311 GO->getSection() + "': " + toString(std::move(E)) + "."); 0
1312 } 0
1313 ----
1314 // Get the section. ----
1315 MCSectionMachO *S = ----
1316 getContext().getMachOSection(Segment, Section, TAA, StubSize, Kind); 0
1317 ----
1318 // If TAA wasn't set by ParseSectionSpecifier() above, ----
1319 // use the value returned by getMachOSection() as a default. ----
1320 if (!TAAParsed) 0
1321 TAA = S->getTypeAndAttributes(); 0
1322 ----
1323 // Okay, now that we got the section, verify that the TAA & StubSize agree. ----
1324 // If the user declared multiple globals with different section flags, we need ----
1325 // to reject it here. ----
1326 if (S->getTypeAndAttributes() != TAA || S->getStubSize() != StubSize) { 0
1327 // If invalid, report the error with report_fatal_error. ----
1328 report_fatal_error("Global variable '" + GO->getName() + 0
1329 "' section type or attributes does not match previous" ----
1330 " section specifier"); 0
1331 } ----
1332 ----
1333 return S; 0
1334 } ----
1335 ----
1336 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileMachO::SelectSectionForGlobal( 0
1337 const GlobalObject *GO, SectionKind Kind, const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
1338 checkMachOComdat(GO); 0
1339 ----
1340 // Handle thread local data. ----
1341 if (Kind.isThreadBSS()) return TLSBSSSection; 0
1342 if (Kind.isThreadData()) return TLSDataSection; 0
1343 ----
1344 if (Kind.isText()) 0
1345 return GO->isWeakForLinker() ? TextCoalSection : TextSection; 0
1346 ----
1347 // If this is weak/linkonce, put this in a coalescable section, either in text ----
1348 // or data depending on if it is writable. ----
1349 if (GO->isWeakForLinker()) { 0
1350 if (Kind.isReadOnly()) 0
1351 return ConstTextCoalSection; 0
1352 if (Kind.isReadOnlyWithRel()) 0
1353 return ConstDataCoalSection; 0
1354 return DataCoalSection; 0
1355 } ----
1356 ----
1357 // FIXME: Alignment check should be handled by section classifier. ----
1358 if (Kind.isMergeable1ByteCString() && 0
1359 GO->getParent()->getDataLayout().getPreferredAlign( 0
1360 cast(GO)) < Align(32)) 0
1361 return CStringSection; 0
1362 ----
1363 // Do not put 16-bit arrays in the UString section if they have an ----
1364 // externally visible label, this runs into issues with certain linker ----
1365 // versions. ----
1366 if (Kind.isMergeable2ByteCString() && !GO->hasExternalLinkage() && 0
1367 GO->getParent()->getDataLayout().getPreferredAlign( 0
1368 cast(GO)) < Align(32)) 0
1369 return UStringSection; 0
1370 ----
1371 // With MachO only variables whose corresponding symbol starts with 'l' or ----
1372 // 'L' can be merged, so we only try merging GVs with private linkage. ----
1373 if (GO->hasPrivateLinkage() && Kind.isMergeableConst()) { 0
1374 if (Kind.isMergeableConst4()) 0
1375 return FourByteConstantSection; 0
1376 if (Kind.isMergeableConst8()) 0
1377 return EightByteConstantSection; 0
1378 if (Kind.isMergeableConst16()) 0
1379 return SixteenByteConstantSection; 0
1380 } ----
1381 ----
1382 // Otherwise, if it is readonly, but not something we can specially optimize, ----
1383 // just drop it in .const. ----
1384 if (Kind.isReadOnly()) 0
1385 return ReadOnlySection; 0
1386 ----
1387 // If this is marked const, put it into a const section. But if the dynamic ----
1388 // linker needs to write to it, put it in the data segment. ----
1389 if (Kind.isReadOnlyWithRel()) 0
1390 return ConstDataSection; 0
1391 ----
1392 // Put zero initialized globals with strong external linkage in the ----
1393 // DATA, __common section with the .zerofill directive. ----
1394 if (Kind.isBSSExtern()) 0
1395 return DataCommonSection; 0
1396 ----
1397 // Put zero initialized globals with local linkage in __DATA,__bss directive ----
1398 // with the .zerofill directive (aka .lcomm). ----
1399 if (Kind.isBSSLocal()) 0
1400 return DataBSSSection; 0
1401 ----
1402 // Otherwise, just drop the variable in the normal data section. ----
1403 return DataSection; 0
1404 } ----
1405 ----
1406 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileMachO::getSectionForConstant( 0
1407 const DataLayout &DL, SectionKind Kind, const Constant *C, ----
1408 Align &Alignment) const { ----
1409 // If this constant requires a relocation, we have to put it in the data ----
1410 // segment, not in the text segment. ----
1411 if (Kind.isData() || Kind.isReadOnlyWithRel()) 0
1412 return ConstDataSection; 0
1413 ----
1414 if (Kind.isMergeableConst4()) 0
1415 return FourByteConstantSection; 0
1416 if (Kind.isMergeableConst8()) 0
1417 return EightByteConstantSection; 0
1418 if (Kind.isMergeableConst16()) 0
1419 return SixteenByteConstantSection; 0
1420 return ReadOnlySection; // .const 0
1421 } ----
1422 ----
1423 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileMachO::getSectionForCommandLines() const { 0
1424 return getContext().getMachOSection("__TEXT", "__command_line", 0, 0
1425 SectionKind::getReadOnly()); 0
1426 } ----
1427 ----
1428 const MCExpr *TargetLoweringObjectFileMachO::getTTypeGlobalReference( 0
1429 const GlobalValue *GV, unsigned Encoding, const TargetMachine &TM, ----
1430 MachineModuleInfo *MMI, MCStreamer &Streamer) const { ----
1431 // The mach-o version of this method defaults to returning a stub reference. ----
1432 ----
1433 if (Encoding & DW_EH_PE_indirect) { 0
1434 MachineModuleInfoMachO &MachOMMI = ----
1435 MMI->getObjFileInfo(); 0
1436 ----
1437 MCSymbol *SSym = getSymbolWithGlobalValueBase(GV, "$non_lazy_ptr", TM); 0
1438 ----
1439 // Add information about the stub reference to MachOMMI so that the stub ----
1440 // gets emitted by the asmprinter. ----
1441 MachineModuleInfoImpl::StubValueTy &StubSym = MachOMMI.getGVStubEntry(SSym); 0
1442 if (!StubSym.getPointer()) { 0
1443 MCSymbol *Sym = TM.getSymbol(GV); 0
1444 StubSym = MachineModuleInfoImpl::StubValueTy(Sym, !GV->hasLocalLinkage()); 0
1445 } ----
1446 ----
1447 return TargetLoweringObjectFile:: ----
1448 getTTypeReference(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(SSym, getContext()), 0
1449 Encoding & ~DW_EH_PE_indirect, Streamer); 0
1450 } ----
1451 ----
1452 return TargetLoweringObjectFile::getTTypeGlobalReference(GV, Encoding, TM, 0
1453 MMI, Streamer); 0
1454 } ----
1455 ----
1456 MCSymbol *TargetLoweringObjectFileMachO::getCFIPersonalitySymbol( 0
1457 const GlobalValue *GV, const TargetMachine &TM, ----
1458 MachineModuleInfo *MMI) const { ----
1459 // The mach-o version of this method defaults to returning a stub reference. ----
1460 MachineModuleInfoMachO &MachOMMI = ----
1461 MMI->getObjFileInfo(); 0
1462 ----
1463 MCSymbol *SSym = getSymbolWithGlobalValueBase(GV, "$non_lazy_ptr", TM); 0
1464 ----
1465 // Add information about the stub reference to MachOMMI so that the stub ----
1466 // gets emitted by the asmprinter. ----
1467 MachineModuleInfoImpl::StubValueTy &StubSym = MachOMMI.getGVStubEntry(SSym); 0
1468 if (!StubSym.getPointer()) { 0
1469 MCSymbol *Sym = TM.getSymbol(GV); 0
1470 StubSym = MachineModuleInfoImpl::StubValueTy(Sym, !GV->hasLocalLinkage()); 0
1471 } ----

1473 return SSym; 0
1474 } ----
1475 ----
1476 const MCExpr *TargetLoweringObjectFileMachO::getIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel( 0
1477 const GlobalValue *GV, const MCSymbol *Sym, const MCValue &MV, ----
1478 int64_t Offset, MachineModuleInfo *MMI, MCStreamer &Streamer) const { ----
1479 // Although MachO 32-bit targets do not explicitly have a GOTPCREL relocation ----
1480 // as 64-bit do, we replace the GOT equivalent by accessing the final symbol ----
1481 // through a non_lazy_ptr stub instead. One advantage is that it allows the ----
1482 // computation of deltas to final external symbols. Example: ----
1483 // ----
1484 // _extgotequiv: ----
1485 // .long _extfoo ----
1486 // ----
1487 // _delta: ----
1488 // .long _extgotequiv-_delta ----
1489 // ----
1490 // is transformed to: ----
1491 // ----
1492 // _delta: ----
1493 // .long L_extfoo$non_lazy_ptr-(_delta+0) ----
1494 // ----
1495 // .section __IMPORT,__pointers,non_lazy_symbol_pointers ----
1496 // L_extfoo$non_lazy_ptr: ----
1497 // .indirect_symbol _extfoo ----
1498 // .long 0 ----
1499 // ----
1500 // The indirect symbol table (and sections of non_lazy_symbol_pointers type) ----
1501 // may point to both local (same translation unit) and global (other ----
1502 // translation units) symbols. Example: ----
1503 // ----
1504 // .section __DATA,__pointers,non_lazy_symbol_pointers ----
1505 // L1: ----
1506 // .indirect_symbol _myGlobal ----
1507 // .long 0 ----
1508 // L2: ----
1509 // .indirect_symbol _myLocal ----
1510 // .long _myLocal ----
1511 // ----
1512 // If the symbol is local, instead of the symbol's index, the assembler ----
1513 // places the constant INDIRECT_SYMBOL_LOCAL into the indirect symbol table. ----
1514 // Then the linker will notice the constant in the table and will look at the ----
1515 // content of the symbol. ----
1516 MachineModuleInfoMachO &MachOMMI = ----
1517 MMI->getObjFileInfo(); 0
1518 MCContext &Ctx = getContext(); 0
1519 ----
1520 // The offset must consider the original displacement from the base symbol ----
1521 // since 32-bit targets don't have a GOTPCREL to fold the PC displacement. ----
1522 Offset = -MV.getConstant(); 0
1523 const MCSymbol *BaseSym = &MV.getSymB()->getSymbol(); 0
1524 ----
1525 // Access the final symbol via sym$non_lazy_ptr and generate the appropriated ----
1526 // non_lazy_ptr stubs. ----
1527 SmallString<128> Name; 0
1528 StringRef Suffix = "$non_lazy_ptr"; 0
1529 Name += MMI->getModule()->getDataLayout().getPrivateGlobalPrefix(); 0
1530 Name += Sym->getName(); 0
1531 Name += Suffix; 0
1532 MCSymbol *Stub = Ctx.getOrCreateSymbol(Name); 0
1533 ----
1534 MachineModuleInfoImpl::StubValueTy &StubSym = MachOMMI.getGVStubEntry(Stub); 0
1535 ----
1536 if (!StubSym.getPointer()) 0
1537 StubSym = MachineModuleInfoImpl::StubValueTy(const_cast(Sym), 0
1538 !GV->hasLocalLinkage()); 0
1539 ----
1540 const MCExpr *BSymExpr = ----
1541 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(BaseSym, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, Ctx); 0
1542 const MCExpr *LHS = ----
1543 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Stub, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, Ctx); 0
1544 ----
1545 if (!Offset) 0
1546 return MCBinaryExpr::createSub(LHS, BSymExpr, Ctx); 0
1547 ----
1548 const MCExpr *RHS = ----
1549 MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(BSymExpr, MCConstantExpr::create(Offset, Ctx), Ctx); 0
1550 return MCBinaryExpr::createSub(LHS, RHS, Ctx); 0
1551 } 0
1552 ----
1553 static bool canUsePrivateLabel(const MCAsmInfo &AsmInfo, 0
1554 const MCSection &Section) { ----
1555 if (!AsmInfo.isSectionAtomizableBySymbols(Section)) 0
1556 return true; 0
1557 ----
1558 // FIXME: we should be able to use private labels for sections that can't be ----
1559 // dead-stripped (there's no issue with blocking atomization there), but `ld ----
1560 // -r` sometimes drops the no_dead_strip attribute from sections so for safety ----
1561 // we don't allow it. ----
1562 return false; 0
1563 } ----
1564 ----
1565 void TargetLoweringObjectFileMachO::getNameWithPrefix( 0
1566 SmallVectorImpl &OutName, const GlobalValue *GV, ----
1567 const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
1568 bool CannotUsePrivateLabel = true; 0
1569 if (auto *GO = GV->getAliaseeObject()) { 0
1570 SectionKind GOKind = TargetLoweringObjectFile::getKindForGlobal(GO, TM); 0
1571 const MCSection *TheSection = SectionForGlobal(GO, GOKind, TM); 0
1572 CannotUsePrivateLabel = 0
1573 !canUsePrivateLabel(*TM.getMCAsmInfo(), *TheSection); 0
1574 } ----
1575 getMangler().getNameWithPrefix(OutName, GV, CannotUsePrivateLabel); 0
1576 } 0

1582 static unsigned ----
1583 getCOFFSectionFlags(SectionKind K, const TargetMachine &TM) { 0
1584 unsigned Flags = 0; 0
1585 bool isThumb = TM.getTargetTriple().getArch() == Triple::thumb; 0
1586 ----
1587 if (K.isMetadata()) 0
1588 Flags |= 0
1589 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_DISCARDABLE; ----
1590 else if (K.isExclude()) 0
1591 Flags |= 0
1592 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_LNK_REMOVE | COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_DISCARDABLE; ----
1593 else if (K.isText()) 0
1594 Flags |= 0
1595 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_EXECUTE | ----
1596 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ | ----
1597 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_CNT_CODE | 0
1598 (isThumb ? COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_16BIT : (COFF::SectionCharacteristics)0); ----
1599 else if (K.isBSS()) 0
1600 Flags |= 0
1601 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_CNT_UNINITIALIZED_DATA | ----
1602 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ | ----
1603 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_WRITE; ----
1604 else if (K.isThreadLocal()) 0
1605 Flags |= 0
1606 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_CNT_INITIALIZED_DATA | ----
1607 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ | ----
1608 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_WRITE; ----
1609 else if (K.isReadOnly() || K.isReadOnlyWithRel()) 0
1610 Flags |= 0
1611 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_CNT_INITIALIZED_DATA | ----
1612 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ; ----
1613 else if (K.isWriteable()) 0
1614 Flags |= 0
1615 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_CNT_INITIALIZED_DATA | ----
1616 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ | ----
1617 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_WRITE; ----
1618 ----
1619 return Flags; 0
1620 } ----
1621 ----
1622 static const GlobalValue *getComdatGVForCOFF(const GlobalValue *GV) { 0
1623 const Comdat *C = GV->getComdat(); 0
1624 assert(C && "expected GV to have a Comdat!"); 0
1625 ----
1626 StringRef ComdatGVName = C->getName(); 0
1627 const GlobalValue *ComdatGV = GV->getParent()->getNamedValue(ComdatGVName); 0
1628 if (!ComdatGV) 0
1629 report_fatal_error("Associative COMDAT symbol '" + ComdatGVName + 0
1630 "' does not exist."); 0
1631 ----
1632 if (ComdatGV->getComdat() != C) 0
1633 report_fatal_error("Associative COMDAT symbol '" + ComdatGVName + 0
1634 "' is not a key for its COMDAT."); 0
1635 ----
1636 return ComdatGV; 0
1637 } ----
1638 ----
1639 static int getSelectionForCOFF(const GlobalValue *GV) { 0
1640 if (const Comdat *C = GV->getComdat()) { 0
1641 const GlobalValue *ComdatKey = getComdatGVForCOFF(GV); 0
1642 if (const auto *GA = dyn_cast(ComdatKey)) 0
1643 ComdatKey = GA->getAliaseeObject(); 0
1644 if (ComdatKey == GV) { 0
1645 switch (C->getSelectionKind()) { 0
1646 case Comdat::Any: 0
1647 return COFF::IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_ANY; 0
1648 case Comdat::ExactMatch: 0
1649 return COFF::IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_EXACT_MATCH; 0
1650 case Comdat::Largest: 0
1651 return COFF::IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_LARGEST; 0
1652 case Comdat::NoDeduplicate: 0
1653 return COFF::IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_NODUPLICATES; 0
1654 case Comdat::SameSize: 0
1655 return COFF::IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_SAME_SIZE; 0
1656 } ----
1657 } else { ----
1658 return COFF::IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_ASSOCIATIVE; 0
1659 } ----
1660 } ----
1661 return 0; 0
1662 } ----
1663 ----
1664 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileCOFF::getExplicitSectionGlobal( 0
1665 const GlobalObject *GO, SectionKind Kind, const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
1666 int Selection = 0; 0
1667 unsigned Characteristics = getCOFFSectionFlags(Kind, TM); 0
1668 StringRef Name = GO->getSection(); 0
1669 StringRef COMDATSymName = ""; 0
1670 if (GO->hasComdat()) { 0
1671 Selection = getSelectionForCOFF(GO); 0
1672 const GlobalValue *ComdatGV; ----
1673 if (Selection == COFF::IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_ASSOCIATIVE) 0
1674 ComdatGV = getComdatGVForCOFF(GO); 0
1675 else ----
1676 ComdatGV = GO; 0
1677 ----
1678 if (!ComdatGV->hasPrivateLinkage()) { 0
1679 MCSymbol *Sym = TM.getSymbol(ComdatGV); 0
1680 COMDATSymName = Sym->getName(); 0
1681 Characteristics |= COFF::IMAGE_SCN_LNK_COMDAT; 0
1682 } else { ----
1683 Selection = 0; 0
1684 } ----
1685 } ----
1686 ----
1687 return getContext().getCOFFSection(Name, Characteristics, Kind, COMDATSymName, 0
1688 Selection); 0
1689 } ----
1690 ----
1691 static StringRef getCOFFSectionNameForUniqueGlobal(SectionKind Kind) { 0
1692 if (Kind.isText()) 0
1693 return ".text"; 0
1694 if (Kind.isBSS()) 0
1695 return ".bss"; 0
1696 if (Kind.isThreadLocal()) 0
1697 return ".tls$"; 0
1698 if (Kind.isReadOnly() || Kind.isReadOnlyWithRel()) 0
1699 return ".rdata"; 0
1700 return ".data"; 0
1701 } ----
1702 ----
1703 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileCOFF::SelectSectionForGlobal( 0
1704 const GlobalObject *GO, SectionKind Kind, const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
1705 // If we have -ffunction-sections then we should emit the global value to a ----
1706 // uniqued section specifically for it. ----
1707 bool EmitUniquedSection; ----
1708 if (Kind.isText()) 0
1709 EmitUniquedSection = TM.getFunctionSections(); 0
1710 else ----
1711 EmitUniquedSection = TM.getDataSections(); 0
1712 ----
1713 if ((EmitUniquedSection && !Kind.isCommon()) || GO->hasComdat()) { 0
1714 SmallString<256> Name = getCOFFSectionNameForUniqueGlobal(Kind); 0
1715 ----
1716 unsigned Characteristics = getCOFFSectionFlags(Kind, TM); 0
1717 ----
1718 Characteristics |= COFF::IMAGE_SCN_LNK_COMDAT; 0
1719 int Selection = getSelectionForCOFF(GO); 0
1720 if (!Selection) 0
1721 Selection = COFF::IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_NODUPLICATES; 0
1722 const GlobalValue *ComdatGV; ----
1723 if (GO->hasComdat()) 0
1724 ComdatGV = getComdatGVForCOFF(GO); 0
1725 else ----
1726 ComdatGV = GO; 0
1727 ----
1728 unsigned UniqueID = MCContext::GenericSectionID; 0
1729 if (EmitUniquedSection) 0
1730 UniqueID = NextUniqueID++; 0
1731 ----
1732 if (!ComdatGV->hasPrivateLinkage()) { 0
1733 MCSymbol *Sym = TM.getSymbol(ComdatGV); 0
1734 StringRef COMDATSymName = Sym->getName(); 0
1735 ----
1736 if (const auto *F = dyn_cast(GO)) 0
1737 if (std::optional Prefix = F->getSectionPrefix()) 0
1738 raw_svector_ostream(Name) << '$' << *Prefix; 0
1739 ----
1740 // Append "$symbol" to the section name *before* IR-level mangling is ----
1741 // applied when targetting mingw. This is what GCC does, and the ld.bfd ----
1742 // COFF linker will not properly handle comdats otherwise. ----
1743 if (getContext().getTargetTriple().isWindowsGNUEnvironment()) 0
1744 raw_svector_ostream(Name) << '$' << ComdatGV->getName(); 0
1745 ----
1746 return getContext().getCOFFSection(Name, Characteristics, Kind, 0
1747 COMDATSymName, Selection, UniqueID); 0
1748 } else { ----
1749 SmallString<256> TmpData; 0
1750 getMangler().getNameWithPrefix(TmpData, GO, /*CannotUsePrivateLabel=*/true); 0
1751 return getContext().getCOFFSection(Name, Characteristics, Kind, TmpData, 0
1752 Selection, UniqueID); 0
1753 } 0
1754 } 0
1755 ----
1756 if (Kind.isText()) 0
1757 return TextSection; 0
1758 ----
1759 if (Kind.isThreadLocal()) 0
1760 return TLSDataSection; 0
1761 ----
1762 if (Kind.isReadOnly() || Kind.isReadOnlyWithRel()) 0
1763 return ReadOnlySection; 0
1764 ----
1765 // Note: we claim that common symbols are put in BSSSection, but they are ----
1766 // really emitted with the magic .comm directive, which creates a symbol table ----
1767 // entry but not a section. ----
1768 if (Kind.isBSS() || Kind.isCommon()) 0
1769 return BSSSection; 0
1770 ----
1771 return DataSection; 0
1772 } ----
1773 ----
1774 void TargetLoweringObjectFileCOFF::getNameWithPrefix( 0
1775 SmallVectorImpl &OutName, const GlobalValue *GV, ----
1776 const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
1777 bool CannotUsePrivateLabel = false; 0
1778 if (GV->hasPrivateLinkage() && 0
1779 ((isa(GV) && TM.getFunctionSections()) || 0
1780 (isa(GV) && TM.getDataSections()))) 0
1781 CannotUsePrivateLabel = true; 0
1782 ----
1783 getMangler().getNameWithPrefix(OutName, GV, CannotUsePrivateLabel); 0
1784 } 0
1785 ----
1786 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileCOFF::getSectionForJumpTable( 0
1787 const Function &F, const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
1788 // If the function can be removed, produce a unique section so that ----
1789 // the table doesn't prevent the removal. ----
1790 const Comdat *C = F.getComdat(); 0
1791 bool EmitUniqueSection = TM.getFunctionSections() || C; 0
1792 if (!EmitUniqueSection) 0
1793 return ReadOnlySection; 0
1794 ----
1795 // FIXME: we should produce a symbol for F instead. ----
1796 if (F.hasPrivateLinkage()) 0
1797 return ReadOnlySection; 0
1798 ----
1799 MCSymbol *Sym = TM.getSymbol(&F); 0
1800 StringRef COMDATSymName = Sym->getName(); 0
1801 ----
1802 SectionKind Kind = SectionKind::getReadOnly(); 0
1803 StringRef SecName = getCOFFSectionNameForUniqueGlobal(Kind); 0
1804 unsigned Characteristics = getCOFFSectionFlags(Kind, TM); 0
1805 Characteristics |= COFF::IMAGE_SCN_LNK_COMDAT; 0
1806 unsigned UniqueID = NextUniqueID++; 0
1807 ----
1808 return getContext().getCOFFSection( 0
1809 SecName, Characteristics, Kind, COMDATSymName, ----
1810 COFF::IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_ASSOCIATIVE, UniqueID); 0
1811 } ----
1812 ----
1813 bool TargetLoweringObjectFileCOFF::shouldPutJumpTableInFunctionSection( 0
1814 bool UsesLabelDifference, const Function &F) const { ----
1815 if (TM->getTargetTriple().getArch() == Triple::x86_64) { 0
1816 if (!JumpTableInFunctionSection) { 0
1817 // We can always create relative relocations, so use another section ----
1818 // that can be marked non-executable. ----
1819 return false; 0
1820 } ----
1821 } ----
1822 return TargetLoweringObjectFile::shouldPutJumpTableInFunctionSection( 0
1823 UsesLabelDifference, F); 0
1824 } ----
1825 ----
1826 void TargetLoweringObjectFileCOFF::emitModuleMetadata(MCStreamer &Streamer, 0
1827 Module &M) const { ----
1828 emitLinkerDirectives(Streamer, M); 0
1829 ----
1830 unsigned Version = 0; 0
1831 unsigned Flags = 0; 0
1832 StringRef Section; 0
1833 ----
1834 GetObjCImageInfo(M, Version, Flags, Section); 0
1835 if (!Section.empty()) { 0
1836 auto &C = getContext(); 0
1837 auto *S = C.getCOFFSection(Section, 0
1838 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_CNT_INITIALIZED_DATA | ----
1839 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ, ----
1840 SectionKind::getReadOnly()); ----
1841 Streamer.switchSection(S); 0
1842 Streamer.emitLabel(C.getOrCreateSymbol(StringRef("OBJC_IMAGE_INFO"))); 0
1843 Streamer.emitInt32(Version); 0
1844 Streamer.emitInt32(Flags); 0
1845 Streamer.addBlankLine(); 0
1846 } ----
1847 ----
1848 emitCGProfileMetadata(Streamer, M); 0
1849 } 0
1850 ----
1851 void TargetLoweringObjectFileCOFF::emitLinkerDirectives( 0
1852 MCStreamer &Streamer, Module &M) const { ----
1853 if (NamedMDNode *LinkerOptions = M.getNamedMetadata("llvm.linker.options")) { 0
1854 // Emit the linker options to the linker .drectve section. According to the ----
1855 // spec, this section is a space-separated string containing flags for ----
1856 // linker. ----
1857 MCSection *Sec = getDrectveSection(); 0
1858 Streamer.switchSection(Sec); 0
1859 for (const auto *Option : LinkerOptions->operands()) { 0
1860 for (const auto &Piece : cast(Option)->operands()) { 0
1861 // Lead with a space for consistency with our dllexport implementation. ----
1862 std::string Directive(" "); 0
1863 Directive.append(std::string(cast(Piece)->getString())); 0
1864 Streamer.emitBytes(Directive); 0
1865 } 0
1866 } ----
1867 } ----
1868 ----
1869 // Emit /EXPORT: flags for each exported global as necessary. ----
1870 std::string Flags; 0
1871 for (const GlobalValue &GV : M.global_values()) { 0
1872 raw_string_ostream OS(Flags); 0
1873 emitLinkerFlagsForGlobalCOFF(OS, &GV, getContext().getTargetTriple(), 0
1874 getMangler()); ----
1875 OS.flush(); 0
1876 if (!Flags.empty()) { 0
1877 Streamer.switchSection(getDrectveSection()); 0
1878 Streamer.emitBytes(Flags); 0
1879 } ----
1880 Flags.clear(); 0
1881 } 0
1882 ----
1883 // Emit /INCLUDE: flags for each used global as necessary. ----
1884 if (const auto *LU = M.getNamedGlobal("llvm.used")) { 0
1885 assert(LU->hasInitializer() && "expected llvm.used to have an initializer"); 0
1886 assert(isa(LU->getValueType()) && 0
1887 "expected llvm.used to be an array type"); ----
1888 if (const auto *A = cast(LU->getInitializer())) { 0
1889 for (const Value *Op : A->operands()) { 0
1890 const auto *GV = cast(Op->stripPointerCasts()); 0
1891 // Global symbols with internal or private linkage are not visible to ----
1892 // the linker, and thus would cause an error when the linker tried to ----
1893 // preserve the symbol due to the `/include:` directive. ----
1894 if (GV->hasLocalLinkage()) 0
1895 continue; 0
1896 ----
1897 raw_string_ostream OS(Flags); 0
1898 emitLinkerFlagsForUsedCOFF(OS, GV, getContext().getTargetTriple(), 0
1899 getMangler()); ----
1900 OS.flush(); 0
1901 ----
1902 if (!Flags.empty()) { 0
1903 Streamer.switchSection(getDrectveSection()); 0
1904 Streamer.emitBytes(Flags); 0
1905 } ----
1906 Flags.clear(); 0
1907 } 0
1908 } ----
1909 } ----
1910 } 0
1911 ----
1912 void TargetLoweringObjectFileCOFF::Initialize(MCContext &Ctx, 0
1913 const TargetMachine &TM) { ----
1914 TargetLoweringObjectFile::Initialize(Ctx, TM); 0
1915 this->TM = &TM; 0
1916 const Triple &T = TM.getTargetTriple(); 0
1917 if (T.isWindowsMSVCEnvironment() || T.isWindowsItaniumEnvironment()) { 0
1918 StaticCtorSection = 0
1919 Ctx.getCOFFSection(".CRT$XCU", COFF::IMAGE_SCN_CNT_INITIALIZED_DATA | 0
1920 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ, ----
1921 SectionKind::getReadOnly()); ----
1922 StaticDtorSection = 0
1923 Ctx.getCOFFSection(".CRT$XTX", COFF::IMAGE_SCN_CNT_INITIALIZED_DATA | 0
1924 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ, ----
1925 SectionKind::getReadOnly()); ----
1926 } else { ----
1927 StaticCtorSection = Ctx.getCOFFSection( 0
1928 ".ctors", COFF::IMAGE_SCN_CNT_INITIALIZED_DATA | ----
1929 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ | COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_WRITE, ----
1930 SectionKind::getData()); ----
1931 StaticDtorSection = Ctx.getCOFFSection( 0
1932 ".dtors", COFF::IMAGE_SCN_CNT_INITIALIZED_DATA | ----
1933 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ | COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_WRITE, ----
1934 SectionKind::getData()); ----
1935 } ----
1936 } 0
1937 ----
1938 static MCSectionCOFF *getCOFFStaticStructorSection(MCContext &Ctx, 0
1939 const Triple &T, bool IsCtor, ----
1940 unsigned Priority, ----
1941 const MCSymbol *KeySym, ----
1942 MCSectionCOFF *Default) { ----
1943 if (T.isWindowsMSVCEnvironment() || T.isWindowsItaniumEnvironment()) { 0
1944 // If the priority is the default, use .CRT$XCU, possibly associative. ----
1945 if (Priority == 65535) 0
1946 return Ctx.getAssociativeCOFFSection(Default, KeySym, 0); 0
1947 ----
1948 // Otherwise, we need to compute a new section name. Low priorities should ----
1949 // run earlier. The linker will sort sections ASCII-betically, and we need a ----
1950 // string that sorts between .CRT$XCA and .CRT$XCU. In the general case, we ----
1951 // make a name like ".CRT$XCT12345", since that runs before .CRT$XCU. Really ----
1952 // low priorities need to sort before 'L', since the CRT uses that ----
1953 // internally, so we use ".CRT$XCA00001" for them. We have a contract with ----
1954 // the frontend that "init_seg(compiler)" corresponds to priority 200 and ----
1955 // "init_seg(lib)" corresponds to priority 400, and those respectively use ----
1956 // 'C' and 'L' without the priority suffix. Priorities between 200 and 400 ----
1957 // use 'C' with the priority as a suffix. ----
1958 SmallString<24> Name; 0
1959 char LastLetter = 'T'; 0
1960 bool AddPrioritySuffix = Priority != 200 && Priority != 400; 0
1961 if (Priority < 200) 0
1962 LastLetter = 'A'; 0
1963 else if (Priority < 400) 0
1964 LastLetter = 'C'; 0
1965 else if (Priority == 400) 0
1966 LastLetter = 'L'; 0
1967 raw_svector_ostream OS(Name); 0
1968 OS << ".CRT$X" << (IsCtor ? "C" : "T") << LastLetter; 0
1969 if (AddPrioritySuffix) 0
1970 OS << format("%05u", Priority); 0
1971 MCSectionCOFF *Sec = Ctx.getCOFFSection( 0
1972 Name, COFF::IMAGE_SCN_CNT_INITIALIZED_DATA | COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ, ----
1973 SectionKind::getReadOnly()); ----
1974 return Ctx.getAssociativeCOFFSection(Sec, KeySym, 0); 0
1975 } 0
1976 ----
1977 std::string Name = IsCtor ? ".ctors" : ".dtors"; 0
1978 if (Priority != 65535) 0
1979 raw_string_ostream(Name) << format(".%05u", 65535 - Priority); 0
1980 ----
1981 return Ctx.getAssociativeCOFFSection( 0
1982 Ctx.getCOFFSection(Name, COFF::IMAGE_SCN_CNT_INITIALIZED_DATA | ----
1983 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ | ----
1984 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_WRITE, ----
1985 SectionKind::getData()), ----
1986 KeySym, 0); 0

2002 ----
2003 const MCExpr *TargetLoweringObjectFileCOFF::lowerRelativeReference( 0
2004 const GlobalValue *LHS, const GlobalValue *RHS, ----
2005 const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
2006 const Triple &T = TM.getTargetTriple(); 0
2007 if (T.isOSCygMing()) 0
2008 return nullptr; 0
2009 ----
2010 // Our symbols should exist in address space zero, cowardly no-op if ----
2011 // otherwise. ----
2012 if (LHS->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() != 0 || 0
2013 RHS->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() != 0) 0
2014 return nullptr; 0
2015 ----
2016 // Both ptrtoint instructions must wrap global objects: ----
2017 // - Only global variables are eligible for image relative relocations. ----
2018 // - The subtrahend refers to the special symbol __ImageBase, a GlobalVariable. ----
2019 // We expect __ImageBase to be a global variable without a section, externally ----
2020 // defined. ----
2021 // ----
2022 // It should look something like this: @__ImageBase = external constant i8 ----
2023 if (!isa(LHS) || !isa(RHS) || 0
2024 LHS->isThreadLocal() || RHS->isThreadLocal() || 0
2025 RHS->getName() != "__ImageBase" || !RHS->hasExternalLinkage() || 0
2026 cast(RHS)->hasInitializer() || RHS->hasSection()) 0
2027 return nullptr; 0
2028 ----
2029 return MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TM.getSymbol(LHS), 0
2030 MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_COFF_IMGREL32, ----
2031 getContext()); 0
2032 } ----
2033 ----
2034 static std::string APIntToHexString(const APInt &AI) { 0
2035 unsigned Width = (AI.getBitWidth() / 8) * 2; 0
2036 std::string HexString = toString(AI, 16, /*Signed=*/false); 0
2037 llvm::transform(HexString, HexString.begin(), tolower); 0
2038 unsigned Size = HexString.size(); 0
2039 assert(Width >= Size && "hex string is too large!"); 0
2040 HexString.insert(HexString.begin(), Width - Size, '0'); 0
2041 ----
2042 return HexString; 0
2043 } ----
2044 ----
2045 static std::string scalarConstantToHexString(const Constant *C) { 0
2046 Type *Ty = C->getType(); 0
2047 if (isa(C)) { 0
2048 return APIntToHexString(APInt::getZero(Ty->getPrimitiveSizeInBits())); 0
2049 } else if (const auto *CFP = dyn_cast(C)) { 0
2050 return APIntToHexString(CFP->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt()); 0
2051 } else if (const auto *CI = dyn_cast(C)) { 0
2052 return APIntToHexString(CI->getValue()); 0
2053 } else { ----
2054 unsigned NumElements; ----
2055 if (auto *VTy = dyn_cast(Ty)) 0
2056 NumElements = cast(VTy)->getNumElements(); 0
2057 else ----
2058 NumElements = Ty->getArrayNumElements(); 0
2059 std::string HexString; 0
2060 for (int I = NumElements - 1, E = -1; I != E; --I) 0
2061 HexString += scalarConstantToHexString(C->getAggregateElement(I)); 0
2062 return HexString; 0
2063 } 0
2064 } ----
2065 ----
2066 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileCOFF::getSectionForConstant( 0
2067 const DataLayout &DL, SectionKind Kind, const Constant *C, ----
2068 Align &Alignment) const { ----
2069 if (Kind.isMergeableConst() && C && 0
2070 getContext().getAsmInfo()->hasCOFFComdatConstants()) { 0
2071 // This creates comdat sections with the given symbol name, but unless ----
2072 // AsmPrinter::GetCPISymbol actually makes the symbol global, the symbol ----
2073 // will be created with a null storage class, which makes GNU binutils ----
2074 // error out. ----
2075 const unsigned Characteristics = COFF::IMAGE_SCN_CNT_INITIALIZED_DATA | 0
2076 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ | ----
2077 COFF::IMAGE_SCN_LNK_COMDAT; ----
2078 std::string COMDATSymName; 0
2079 if (Kind.isMergeableConst4()) { 0
2080 if (Alignment <= 4) { 0
2081 COMDATSymName = "__real@" + scalarConstantToHexString(C); 0
2082 Alignment = Align(4); 0
2083 } ----
2084 } else if (Kind.isMergeableConst8()) { 0
2085 if (Alignment <= 8) { 0
2086 COMDATSymName = "__real@" + scalarConstantToHexString(C); 0
2087 Alignment = Align(8); 0
2088 } ----
2089 } else if (Kind.isMergeableConst16()) { 0
2090 // FIXME: These may not be appropriate for non-x86 architectures. ----
2091 if (Alignment <= 16) { 0
2092 COMDATSymName = "__xmm@" + scalarConstantToHexString(C); 0
2093 Alignment = Align(16); 0
2094 } ----
2095 } else if (Kind.isMergeableConst32()) { 0
2096 if (Alignment <= 32) { 0
2097 COMDATSymName = "__ymm@" + scalarConstantToHexString(C); 0
2098 Alignment = Align(32); 0
2099 } ----
2100 } ----
2101 ----
2102 if (!COMDATSymName.empty()) 0
2103 return getContext().getCOFFSection(".rdata", Characteristics, Kind, 0
2104 COMDATSymName, ----
2105 COFF::IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_ANY); 0
2106 } 0
2107 ----
2108 return TargetLoweringObjectFile::getSectionForConstant(DL, Kind, C, 0
2109 Alignment); 0
2110 } ----

2116 static const Comdat *getWasmComdat(const GlobalValue *GV) { 0
2117 const Comdat *C = GV->getComdat(); 0
2118 if (!C) 0
2119 return nullptr; 0
2120 ----
2121 if (C->getSelectionKind() != Comdat::Any) 0
2122 report_fatal_error("WebAssembly COMDATs only support " 0
2123 "SelectionKind::Any, '" + C->getName() + "' cannot be " 0
2124 "lowered."); 0
2125 ----
2126 return C; 0
2127 } ----
2128 ----
2129 static unsigned getWasmSectionFlags(SectionKind K) { 0
2130 unsigned Flags = 0; 0
2131 ----
2132 if (K.isThreadLocal()) 0
2133 Flags |= wasm::WASM_SEG_FLAG_TLS; 0
2134 ----
2135 if (K.isMergeableCString()) 0
2136 Flags |= wasm::WASM_SEG_FLAG_STRINGS; 0
2137 ----
2138 // TODO(sbc): Add suport for K.isMergeableConst() ----
2139 ----
2140 return Flags; 0
2141 } ----
2142 ----
2143 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileWasm::getExplicitSectionGlobal( 0
2144 const GlobalObject *GO, SectionKind Kind, const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
2145 // We don't support explict section names for functions in the wasm object ----
2146 // format. Each function has to be in its own unique section. ----
2147 if (isa(GO)) { 0
2148 return SelectSectionForGlobal(GO, Kind, TM); 0
2149 } ----
2150 ----
2151 StringRef Name = GO->getSection(); 0
2152 ----
2153 // Certain data sections we treat as named custom sections rather than ----
2154 // segments within the data section. ----
2155 // This could be avoided if all data segements (the wasm sense) were ----
2156 // represented as their own sections (in the llvm sense). ----
2157 // TODO(sbc): https://github.com/WebAssembly/tool-conventions/issues/138 ----
2158 if (Name == ".llvmcmd" || Name == ".llvmbc") 0
2159 Kind = SectionKind::getMetadata(); 0
2160 ----
2161 StringRef Group = ""; 0
2162 if (const Comdat *C = getWasmComdat(GO)) { 0
2163 Group = C->getName(); 0
2164 } ----
2165 ----
2166 unsigned Flags = getWasmSectionFlags(Kind); 0
2167 MCSectionWasm *Section = getContext().getWasmSection( 0
2168 Name, Kind, Flags, Group, MCContext::GenericSectionID); ----
2169 ----
2170 return Section; 0
2171 } ----
2172 ----
2173 static MCSectionWasm *selectWasmSectionForGlobal( 0
2174 MCContext &Ctx, const GlobalObject *GO, SectionKind Kind, Mangler &Mang, ----
2175 const TargetMachine &TM, bool EmitUniqueSection, unsigned *NextUniqueID) { ----
2176 StringRef Group = ""; 0
2177 if (const Comdat *C = getWasmComdat(GO)) { 0
2178 Group = C->getName(); 0
2179 } ----
2180 ----
2181 bool UniqueSectionNames = TM.getUniqueSectionNames(); 0
2182 SmallString<128> Name = getSectionPrefixForGlobal(Kind, /*IsLarge=*/false); 0
2183 ----
2184 if (const auto *F = dyn_cast(GO)) { 0
2185 const auto &OptionalPrefix = F->getSectionPrefix(); 0
2186 if (OptionalPrefix) 0
2187 raw_svector_ostream(Name) << '.' << *OptionalPrefix; 0
2188 } ----
2189 ----
2190 if (EmitUniqueSection && UniqueSectionNames) { 0
2191 Name.push_back('.'); 0
2192 TM.getNameWithPrefix(Name, GO, Mang, true); 0
2193 } ----
2194 unsigned UniqueID = MCContext::GenericSectionID; 0
2195 if (EmitUniqueSection && !UniqueSectionNames) { 0
2196 UniqueID = *NextUniqueID; 0
2197 (*NextUniqueID)++; 0
2198 } ----
2199 ----
2200 unsigned Flags = getWasmSectionFlags(Kind); 0
2201 return Ctx.getWasmSection(Name, Kind, Flags, Group, UniqueID); 0
2202 } 0
2203 ----
2204 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileWasm::SelectSectionForGlobal( 0
2205 const GlobalObject *GO, SectionKind Kind, const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
2206 ----
2207 if (Kind.isCommon()) 0
2208 report_fatal_error("mergable sections not supported yet on wasm"); 0
2209 ----
2210 // If we have -ffunction-section or -fdata-section then we should emit the ----
2211 // global value to a uniqued section specifically for it. ----
2212 bool EmitUniqueSection = false; 0
2213 if (Kind.isText()) 0
2214 EmitUniqueSection = TM.getFunctionSections(); 0
2215 else ----
2216 EmitUniqueSection = TM.getDataSections(); 0
2217 EmitUniqueSection |= GO->hasComdat(); 0
2218 ----
2219 return selectWasmSectionForGlobal(getContext(), GO, Kind, getMangler(), TM, 0
2220 EmitUniqueSection, &NextUniqueID); 0
2221 } ----

2233 // We may only use a PLT-relative relocation to refer to unnamed_addr ----

2310 MCSymbol * ----
2311 TargetLoweringObjectFileXCOFF::getTargetSymbol(const GlobalValue *GV, 0
2312 const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
2313 // We always use a qualname symbol for a GV that represents ----
2314 // a declaration, a function descriptor, or a common symbol. ----
2315 // If a GV represents a GlobalVariable and -fdata-sections is enabled, we ----
2316 // also return a qualname so that a label symbol could be avoided. ----
2317 // It is inherently ambiguous when the GO represents the address of a ----
2318 // function, as the GO could either represent a function descriptor or a ----
2319 // function entry point. We choose to always return a function descriptor ----
2320 // here. ----
2321 if (const GlobalObject *GO = dyn_cast(GV)) { 0
2322 if (GO->isDeclarationForLinker()) 0
2323 return cast(getSectionForExternalReference(GO, TM)) 0
2324 ->getQualNameSymbol(); 0
2325 ----
2326 if (const GlobalVariable *GVar = dyn_cast(GV)) 0
2327 if (GVar->hasAttribute("toc-data")) 0
2328 return cast( ----
2329 SectionForGlobal(GVar, SectionKind::getData(), TM)) ----
2330 ->getQualNameSymbol(); 0
2331 ----
2332 SectionKind GOKind = getKindForGlobal(GO, TM); 0
2333 if (GOKind.isText()) 0
2334 return cast( ----
2335 getSectionForFunctionDescriptor(cast(GO), TM)) 0
2336 ->getQualNameSymbol(); 0
2337 if ((TM.getDataSections() && !GO->hasSection()) || GO->hasCommonLinkage() || 0
2338 GOKind.isBSSLocal() || GOKind.isThreadBSSLocal()) 0
2339 return cast(SectionForGlobal(GO, GOKind, TM)) ----
2340 ->getQualNameSymbol(); 0
2341 } ----
2342 ----
2343 // For all other cases, fall back to getSymbol to return the unqualified name. ----
2344 return nullptr; 0
2345 } ----
2346 ----
2347 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileXCOFF::getExplicitSectionGlobal( 0
2348 const GlobalObject *GO, SectionKind Kind, const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
2349 if (!GO->hasSection()) 0
2350 report_fatal_error("#pragma clang section is not yet supported"); 0
2351 ----
2352 StringRef SectionName = GO->getSection(); 0
2353 ----
2354 // Handle the XCOFF::TD case first, then deal with the rest. ----
2355 if (const GlobalVariable *GVar = dyn_cast(GO)) 0
2356 if (GVar->hasAttribute("toc-data")) 0
2357 return getContext().getXCOFFSection( 0
2358 SectionName, Kind, ----
2359 XCOFF::CsectProperties(/*MappingClass*/ XCOFF::XMC_TD, XCOFF::XTY_SD), 0
2360 /* MultiSymbolsAllowed*/ true); 0
2361 ----
2362 XCOFF::StorageMappingClass MappingClass; ----
2363 if (Kind.isText()) 0
2364 MappingClass = XCOFF::XMC_PR; 0
2365 else if (Kind.isData() || Kind.isBSS()) 0
2366 MappingClass = XCOFF::XMC_RW; 0
2367 else if (Kind.isReadOnlyWithRel()) 0
2368 MappingClass = 0
2369 TM.Options.XCOFFReadOnlyPointers ? XCOFF::XMC_RO : XCOFF::XMC_RW; 0
2370 else if (Kind.isReadOnly()) 0
2371 MappingClass = XCOFF::XMC_RO; 0
2372 else ----
2373 report_fatal_error("XCOFF other section types not yet implemented."); 0
2374 ----
2375 return getContext().getXCOFFSection( 0
2376 SectionName, Kind, XCOFF::CsectProperties(MappingClass, XCOFF::XTY_SD), 0
2377 /* MultiSymbolsAllowed*/ true); 0
2378 } ----
2379 ----
2380 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileXCOFF::getSectionForExternalReference( 0
2381 const GlobalObject *GO, const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
2382 assert(GO->isDeclarationForLinker() && 0
2383 "Tried to get ER section for a defined global."); ----
2384 ----
2385 SmallString<128> Name; 0
2386 getNameWithPrefix(Name, GO, TM); 0
2387 ----
2388 XCOFF::StorageMappingClass SMC = ----
2389 isa(GO) ? XCOFF::XMC_DS : XCOFF::XMC_UA; 0
2390 if (GO->isThreadLocal()) 0
2391 SMC = XCOFF::XMC_UL; 0
2392 ----
2393 if (const GlobalVariable *GVar = dyn_cast(GO)) 0
2394 if (GVar->hasAttribute("toc-data")) 0
2395 SMC = XCOFF::XMC_TD; 0
2396 ----
2397 // Externals go into a csect of type ER. ----
2398 return getContext().getXCOFFSection( 0
2399 Name, SectionKind::getMetadata(), ----
2400 XCOFF::CsectProperties(SMC, XCOFF::XTY_ER)); 0
2401 } 0
2402 ----
2403 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileXCOFF::SelectSectionForGlobal( 0
2404 const GlobalObject *GO, SectionKind Kind, const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
2405 // Handle the XCOFF::TD case first, then deal with the rest. ----
2406 if (const GlobalVariable *GVar = dyn_cast(GO)) 0
2407 if (GVar->hasAttribute("toc-data")) { 0
2408 SmallString<128> Name; 0
2409 getNameWithPrefix(Name, GO, TM); 0
2410 return getContext().getXCOFFSection( 0
2411 Name, Kind, XCOFF::CsectProperties(XCOFF::XMC_TD, XCOFF::XTY_SD), 0
2412 /* MultiSymbolsAllowed*/ true); 0
2413 } 0
2414 ----
2415 // Common symbols go into a csect with matching name which will get mapped ----
2416 // into the .bss section. ----
2417 // Zero-initialized local TLS symbols go into a csect with matching name which ----
2418 // will get mapped into the .tbss section. ----
2419 if (Kind.isBSSLocal() || GO->hasCommonLinkage() || Kind.isThreadBSSLocal()) { 0
2420 SmallString<128> Name; 0
2421 getNameWithPrefix(Name, GO, TM); 0
2422 XCOFF::StorageMappingClass SMC = Kind.isBSSLocal() ? XCOFF::XMC_BS 0
2423 : Kind.isCommon() ? XCOFF::XMC_RW 0
2424 : XCOFF::XMC_UL; 0
2425 return getContext().getXCOFFSection( 0
2426 Name, Kind, XCOFF::CsectProperties(SMC, XCOFF::XTY_CM)); 0
2427 } 0
2428 ----
2429 if (Kind.isMergeableCString()) { 0
2430 Align Alignment = GO->getParent()->getDataLayout().getPreferredAlign( 0
2431 cast(GO)); ----
2432 ----
2433 unsigned EntrySize = getEntrySizeForKind(Kind); 0
2434 std::string SizeSpec = ".rodata.str" + utostr(EntrySize) + "."; 0
2435 SmallString<128> Name; 0
2436 Name = SizeSpec + utostr(Alignment.value()); 0
2437 ----
2438 if (TM.getDataSections()) 0
2439 getNameWithPrefix(Name, GO, TM); 0
2440 ----
2441 return getContext().getXCOFFSection( 0
2442 Name, Kind, XCOFF::CsectProperties(XCOFF::XMC_RO, XCOFF::XTY_SD), 0
2443 /* MultiSymbolsAllowed*/ !TM.getDataSections()); 0
2444 } 0
2445 ----
2446 if (Kind.isText()) { 0
2447 if (TM.getFunctionSections()) { 0
2448 return cast(getFunctionEntryPointSymbol(GO, TM)) 0
2449 ->getRepresentedCsect(); 0
2450 } ----
2451 return TextSection; 0
2452 } ----
2453 ----
2454 if (TM.Options.XCOFFReadOnlyPointers && Kind.isReadOnlyWithRel()) { 0
2455 if (!TM.getDataSections()) 0
2456 report_fatal_error( 0
2457 "ReadOnlyPointers is supported only if data sections is turned on"); ----
2458 ----
2459 SmallString<128> Name; 0
2460 getNameWithPrefix(Name, GO, TM); 0
2461 return getContext().getXCOFFSection( 0
2462 Name, SectionKind::getReadOnly(), ----
2463 XCOFF::CsectProperties(XCOFF::XMC_RO, XCOFF::XTY_SD)); 0
2464 } 0
2465 ----
2466 // For BSS kind, zero initialized data must be emitted to the .data section ----
2467 // because external linkage control sections that get mapped to the .bss ----
2468 // section will be linked as tentative defintions, which is only appropriate ----
2469 // for SectionKind::Common. ----
2470 if (Kind.isData() || Kind.isReadOnlyWithRel() || Kind.isBSS()) { 0
2471 if (TM.getDataSections()) { 0
2472 SmallString<128> Name; 0
2473 getNameWithPrefix(Name, GO, TM); 0
2474 return getContext().getXCOFFSection( 0
2475 Name, SectionKind::getData(), ----
2476 XCOFF::CsectProperties(XCOFF::XMC_RW, XCOFF::XTY_SD)); 0
2477 } 0
2478 return DataSection; 0
2479 } ----
2480 ----
2481 if (Kind.isReadOnly()) { 0
2482 if (TM.getDataSections()) { 0
2483 SmallString<128> Name; 0
2484 getNameWithPrefix(Name, GO, TM); 0
2485 return getContext().getXCOFFSection( 0
2486 Name, SectionKind::getReadOnly(), ----
2487 XCOFF::CsectProperties(XCOFF::XMC_RO, XCOFF::XTY_SD)); 0
2488 } 0
2489 return ReadOnlySection; 0
2490 } ----
2491 ----
2492 // External/weak TLS data and initialized local TLS data are not eligible ----
2493 // to be put into common csect. If data sections are enabled, thread ----
2494 // data are emitted into separate sections. Otherwise, thread data ----
2495 // are emitted into the .tdata section. ----
2496 if (Kind.isThreadLocal()) { 0
2497 if (TM.getDataSections()) { 0
2498 SmallString<128> Name; 0
2499 getNameWithPrefix(Name, GO, TM); 0
2500 return getContext().getXCOFFSection( 0
2501 Name, Kind, XCOFF::CsectProperties(XCOFF::XMC_TL, XCOFF::XTY_SD)); 0
2502 } 0
2503 return TLSDataSection; 0
2504 } ----
2505 ----
2506 report_fatal_error("XCOFF other section types not yet implemented."); 0
2507 } ----
2508 ----
2509 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileXCOFF::getSectionForJumpTable( 0
2510 const Function &F, const TargetMachine &TM) const { ----
2511 assert (!F.getComdat() && "Comdat not supported on XCOFF."); 0
2512 ----
2513 if (!TM.getFunctionSections()) 0
2514 return ReadOnlySection; 0
2515 ----
2516 // If the function can be removed, produce a unique section so that ----
2517 // the table doesn't prevent the removal. ----
2518 SmallString<128> NameStr(".rodata.jmp.."); 0
2519 getNameWithPrefix(NameStr, &F, TM); 0

2529 ----
2530 /// Given a mergeable constant with the specified size and relocation ----
2531 /// information, return a section that it should be placed in. ----
2532 MCSection *TargetLoweringObjectFileXCOFF::getSectionForConstant( 0
2533 const DataLayout &DL, SectionKind Kind, const Constant *C, ----
2534 Align &Alignment) const { ----
2535 // TODO: Enable emiting constant pool to unique sections when we support it. ----
2536 if (Alignment > Align(16)) 0
2537 report_fatal_error("Alignments greater than 16 not yet supported."); 0
2538 ----
2539 if (Alignment == Align(8)) { 0
2540 assert(ReadOnly8Section && "Section should always be initialized."); 0
2541 return ReadOnly8Section; 0
2542 } ----
2543 ----
2544 if (Alignment == Align(16)) { 0
2545 assert(ReadOnly16Section && "Section should always be initialized."); 0
2546 return ReadOnly16Section; 0
2547 } ----
2548 ----
2549 return ReadOnlySection; 0
2550 } ----
2551 ----
2552 void TargetLoweringObjectFileXCOFF::Initialize(MCContext &Ctx, 0
2553 const TargetMachine &TgtM) { ----
2554 TargetLoweringObjectFile::Initialize(Ctx, TgtM); 0
2555 TTypeEncoding = 0
